4. ATTRIBUTION

When sharing an icon or other licensed material, including a modified version,
you must provide appropriate attribution.

Where reasonably practicable, attribution should include:

* the title or name of the icon;
* the name or username of its author;
* a reference or link to the original material;
* a reference to the CC BY-SA 4.0 license; and
* an indication of whether the material was modified.

A suitable attribution format is:

```
"[ICON NAME]" by [AUTHOR], from ArchiveTune Icon Pack,
licensed under CC BY-SA 4.0. Changes: [DESCRIPTION OR "none"].
```

Attribution may be provided in application credits, accompanying documentation,
an attribution file, an about page, image metadata, or another reasonable
location appropriate to the medium.

Attribution must not imply that an author, contributor, ArchiveTune, or another
rights holder endorses you or your use of the material.

